summary: I’m a tad sad but I don’t know how to reach out right now because I feel like what I’m dealing with isn’t as important as what...
question: I’m a tad sad but I don’t know how to reach out right now because I feel like what I’m dealing with isn’t as important as what my friends are oop (this was random ’m sorry)
answer:
hey anon !! sorry i’m only just answering and i wanted to say a quick thank you for confiding in me, that means a lot !! 💘💝💗💖

everyone’s problems are important no matter how “big” or “small” they are because they are effecting you. every emotion you feel is valid, no matter the severity of the situation you’re in.

please reach out, i know it can be hard and scary at times but in the long run it will help you, so much. so so much.

humans are a dependent species. that’s how we’re wired. yes some people are good at being independent but ultimately, we can’t do everything alone. we need others. we need to ask for help and that perfectly normal, okay and healthy !! please know if you’re struggling to confide in a friend as of now, you can talk to me. i’m happy to help where ever i can even if it’s just by listening !! but idealistically if it gets too much to handle. talk to an adult, they are the people who are most likely to have the best understanding and advise and they are the people who can take appropriate action when needed.

stay safe and please talk. i know sometimes it can feel like you’re bothering others but believe me you’re not. they’re your friends because they love you on good days and bad. they’re your friends because they want to help you.

you don’t need to worry about talking to them because no matter if you’re problems are “not as important as theirs” they will understand, listen and support you !!❤️
